# Editing index.html

`index.html` is the entire site. Only edit this file; never edit
`Bragg Family Adventure Guide.html` (it's an untracked backup of the original).

## Conventions

- All CSS lives in the single `<style>` block in `<head>`. Add styles there —
  don't create separate `.css` files or add inline `style=""` attributes unless
  matching existing patterns.
- Colors come from the CSS variables in `:root` (`--canyon`, `--rust`, `--sand`,
  `--sage`, `--teal`, `--paper`, `--ink`, `--gold`). Reuse them instead of
  hardcoding new hex values.
- Fonts load from Google Fonts via the `<link>` tags in `<head>`:
  **Passion One** (headings, uppercase), **Nunito** (body), **Caveat**
  (handwritten accents via the `.script` class). To add a font, extend the
  Google Fonts URL rather than adding local font files.
- The page is mobile-friendly (`viewport` meta + fluid layouts). Check that
  changes work at narrow widths.
- No JavaScript is currently used. Prefer keeping the site JS-free unless a
  feature truly needs it.

## Verifying changes

Open the file locally in a browser before pushing:

```bash
open index.html
```
